Of course, I'd be happy to help! Here is an example of how you could implement a `show` method for a struct `FloatWithUnits`:
```
struct FloatWithUnits {
    var value: Float
    var unit: String
}

extension FloatWithUnits {
    func show() -> String {
        return "\(value) \(unit)"
    }
}
```
This will output the value and unit separated by a space, like "1.8 meters".

Alternatively, you could also use `format` method to achieve this:
```
extension FloatWithUnits {
    func show() -> String {
        return Format.floatWithUnit(value: value, unit: unit)
    }
}

private struct Format {
    static func floatWithUnit(value: Float, unit: String) -> String {
        return "\(value) \(unit)"
    }
}
```
This way you can keep the `show` method separate from the implementation of the format string.
